[b]Market Pressure Scale[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]

Splits market activity into two separate oscillators on a 0–100 scale: [b]Setup Pressure[/b] measures how much the market is coiling (ATR/Bollinger compression, proximity to range extremes, relative volume), and [b]Impulse Pressure[/b] measures how much an active move is underway (range expansion, volume, candle body size). A phase label combines both into a single readable state at all times.

[b]Why two components?[/b]

Classic volatility indicators go quiet right when a breakout fires — they cannot detect the impulse. Momentum oscillators do the opposite. This indicator tracks both simultaneously so you can see the full coil-and-release cycle in one panel.

[b]Phases[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Sideways / Chop[/b] — Range Chop Filter active (low ADX, DI+/DI− flat, price mid-range): dead sideways range, takes priority over every other phase
[*][b]Impulse Running[/b] — Impulse above 70: a directional move is active
[*][b]Sideways / Quiet[/b] — both below 40: no setup and no impulse
[/list]

[b]Range Chop Filter[/b]

An ADX/DMI-based chop filter overrides the phase whenever the market is directionless (ADX below 16, DI+ and DI− within 5 of each other) and sitting in the middle of its range, and gates Failed Coil and Reversal so they only evaluate at a genuine range extreme.

[b]Move Strength[/b]

Blue columns (on by default), plotted behind Setup/Impulse Pressure rather than as a full-pane background so they add information without washing out the two curves. Tracks the expected magnitude of the eventual move — not whether a setup exists, but how forceful the release is likely to be once it fires. Built from compression depth, range-edge proximity, and ADX trend confirmation, and suppressed while the Range Chop Filter is active. Colored in 5 opacity bands (near-invisible → faint → medium → strong → near-solid blue) so consecutive bars read as a clear step change rather than a hard-to-read continuous gradient. Also shown as a numeric row in the dashboard table with the same banded cell color.

[b]Signal Markers[/b]

Small labeled markers appear directly on the oscillator with hover tooltips:
[list]
[*][b]Failed Coil FC[/b] — Setup was high but Impulse never confirmed, and price has fallen back toward the middle of the range; breakout stalled
[*][b]Naked Impulse NI[/b] — Impulse running above 70 but Setup has collapsed and ADX is still weak; late-entry warning
[*][b]Reversal ◆[/b] — green (long) or red (short): Impulse fading from its own recent high plus a rejection wick at a range extreme, confirmed by the trigger candle's close, weighted by Setup compression
[/list]
Each marker is individually toggleable.

[b]Reversal[/b]

A counter-trend signal that deliberately avoids DMI. It only activates at a genuine range extreme outside of chop, then combines three weighted components into a single score per direction: how far Impulse Pressure has faded from its own recent high (exhaustion), a rejection wick against the extreme plus a confirming candle close (confirmation), and Setup compression (quality). The signal fires once that score crosses 60 on the correct side of the range.

[b]Dashboard[/b]

A top-right table (off by default, toggle to enable) shows: current phase (color-coded), Setup and Impulse scores with live direction arrows, directional Bias from a configurable MA cross, range position (where price sits within the N-bar high/low range), Move Strength (blue-tinted by magnitude), and a plain-language Action row (Ignore/Chop, Watch Setup, Trend Running, Long/Short Reversal, Wait).

[b]Bias[/b]

Direction is determined by a fast/slow moving average cross with configurable type (EMA, RMA, SMA, WMA, HMA, JMA) and lengths.

[b]Smoothing[/b]

Both output curves can be smoothed independently with any of six MA types (EMA / RMA / SMA / WMA / HMA / JMA) at a configurable length. JMA Phase and Power are also exposed.

[b]Alerts[/b]
All alerts fire only on confirmed bar close by default (configurable via "Alerts only on bar close" toggle).
[list]
[*][b]Impulse Running[/b] — impulse pressure above 70; move is underway
[*][b]Sideways / Quiet[/b] — both pressures low; no directional conviction
[*][b]Signal: Failed Coil[/b] — coil compressed but impulse did not follow
[*][b]Signal: Naked Impulse[/b] — impulse running without a prior coil setup
[*][b]Signal: Reversal Long[/b] / [b]Signal: Reversal Short[/b] — exhaustion + rejection wick at a range extreme
[/list]

